##How to Run the Project Locally##
1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
    git clone https://github.com/sairangasaketh/Employee-Attendance-System.git
cd <your-repo>
2ï¸âƒ£ Install all dependencies
    npm install
(You can use bun install if you prefer Bun.)


4ï¸âƒ£ Start the development server
    npm run dev
This will open your project at:
http://localhost:5173
ğŸ“¦ Production Build
Build:
  npm run build
Preview:
  npm run preview
## Seed Data (Demo Users & Attendance) ##
You can insert sample data into Supabase using SQL:

ğŸ‘¤ Sample Users
sql

INSERT INTO users (id, name, email, role) VALUES
('emp1', 'John Doe', 'john@example.com', 'employee'),
('emp2', 'Alice Smith', 'alice@example.com', 'employee'),
('mgr1', 'Manager One', 'manager@example.com', 'manager');
ğŸ•’ Sample Attendance
sql

INSERT INTO attendance (user_id, date, check_in, check_out, status) VALUES
('emp1', '2025-01-01', '09:05', '17:00', 'present'),
('emp2', '2025-01-01', '09:20', '17:10', 'late');


